title: Formally Hire 0xMaki to Lead Project
body:
Proposed by: @adamscochran

(Remember, these are community proposals. Currently SushiSwap has no formal full time team. All votes must receive overwhelming support from the community, and anyone can make proposals.)

TL;DR:

-SushiSwap doesn't have a full-time team yet.
-0xMaki still has a day job.
-It is time for him to be rewarded for the work he has done as a founder and have him focus on Sushi full time.
-This proposal would give him a one-time founders grant with:
--500k Sushi upfront, and 500k locked over a one-year period as a founders grant.
--A payment of 500k Sushi vested over two-years for continued work on Sushi.
-This would have him as the head of core team focused on building out SushiSwap.
-The community could revoke the additional 500k Sushi if 0xMaki is no longer working on SushiSwap.
-Future votes can establish additional budget and bonuses for Maki if there is strong performance.

Maki will then put forward a plan for SushiSwap, a budget proposal for teams and appointing a core team, and clear guidelines for voting quorums and process to be decided by the community.

The payments on vesting will be approved on a monthly basis (no-cliff) and paid each month by the multisig holders approving the transaction.
